description: Commits must show only the user's git identity — never Cursor as co-author
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git Commit Author

- Commit **Author** and **Committer** must be the user's configured git identity only.
- **Never** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Co-authored-by: cursoragent`, or any Cursor/agent trailer to commit messages.
- **Never** set author/committer name or email to Cursor, cursoragent, or similar.
- When amending or rewriting commits to remove agent attribution, keep the original message subject/body and strip only agent co-author lines, then push with `--force-with-lease` only if the user explicitly asked to fix history on the remote.
